Dear [Potential] Comb User:

The official 1996.0 release of comb, the Bell Labs spectral line reduction
package, is now available for public use.  You MUST have an ANSI C compiler
(gcc will work) to install comb 1996.0. There are 3 ways to get the compressed
(gzip) UNIX tar file of comb 1996.0:

1) via the Comb Page on the World Wide Web
   http://astro.berkeley.edu/pound/comb.html
   
   click on "latest release" to grab the source code.
   click on "manifest file" to grab the file list.

2) anonymous ftp (Note the FTP site has changed. See below)

3) we can send you a tar tape.

 Use the -o option to tar when de-archiving the comb tar file. This prevents 
 owner conflicts in some O/S's.

***********************************************************************
* NOTE: If you have installed a beta version of comb 1996.0 (previous *
* to Sept 10, 1996), then you don't have the official version.        *
***********************************************************************

Comb 1996.0 has been install successfully on the following machines:

	   type                   O/S
	Sparcstation (1-Ultra2) SunOS 4.x, Solaris 2.x
	Sun 4             	SunOS 4.x, Solaris 2.x
	HP 300                  HP-UX
	HP 700                  HP-UX 9.0 (System V)
	PC 386/87 or better     Linux

and should also work on these:

	Sun 3             	SunOS 4.x, Solaris 2.x
	IBM RS6000              AIX       (System V)
	DECstation 5000         Risc Ultrix
	VAX 11/780              BSD

With HISTORY turned off, it may work on
	SGI 			IRIX 5.2

If you have other questions, or wished to be removed from this
mailing list, contact either one of us.

		Sincerely,

